;Introduction
Nuguan' tàj ñaan


;The Internet is becoming an increasingly important part of our lives.
Da’ achîn gui nī nahuin internet ‘ngō sa ña’an doj riña nê’.


;The Mozilla project is a global community of people who believe that openness, innovation, and opportunity are key to the continued health of the Internet. We have worked together since 1998 to ensure that the Internet is developed in a way that benefits everyone. We are best known for creating the Mozilla Firefox web browser.
Riña Mozilla nī ‘iaj sun ‘ngō yi’nïn’ nìko guì anïn ruhuâ sisī da’ui internet gā ni’nïnj man, gā nakà yitïnj man nī gahuin man ‘ngō sa gi’iaj da’ gā ‘ngō sunūnj u. Huè ñûnj gayi’î ‘iaj sun âsij 1998 nī tna’uēj ñûnj da’ gi’iaj sūnūnj internet riña daran’ nê’. Ûta ni’in guìi ñûnj guendâ girirà ñûnj ‘ngō navegador gu’nàj Mozilla Firefox.


;The Mozilla project uses a community-based approach to create world-class open source software and to develop new types of collaborative activities. We create communities of people involved in making the Internet experience better for all of us.
Mozilla nī gi‘iaj sunj ‘ngō sun nuguan’àan da’ ga’ue girij ‘ngō software nikāj ‘ngō código huā ni’nïni ïn nī danj nānj da’ui gīrij a’ngô da’aj nej sun nuguan’àn ga’ue gahuī. Ûta ga’ì yi’nïn’ guìi ‘iaj sun ngà ñûnj yi’ì dan a’ue ûta hue’ê ‘iaj sun internet riña daran’ chre nê’.


;As a result of these efforts, we have distilled a set of principles that we believe are critical for the Internet to continue to benefit the public good as well as commercial aspects of life. We set out these principles below.
‘Ngō sa narugui’ gi’iaj nej sun nuguan’àn nan huin sisī gahuin nùkuaj ñûnj guchrūj ñûnj ‘ngo dukuán tna’uej da’ gi’iaj sunūnj internet riña daran’ guìi, danj nanj ‘iaj sunu riña ‘ngō sun rânj du’uêj e. hìaj nī natà’ ñûnj dàj hua nej dukuán nan.


;The goals for the Manifesto are to:
Nej si chrēj dukuán nan huin:


;articulate a vision for the Internet that Mozilla participants want the Mozilla Foundation to pursue;
Nagi’iaj chre’ nej ñûnj daran’ chre sinuguàn’ nej duguî’ araj sun Mozilla dàj anïn ruhuâ nej si gā Internet nī huê nej nuguan’ dan ganikò’ Fundación Mozilla gan’an.


;speak to people whether or not they have a technical background;
ga’min ñûnj ngà nej guìi si nikāj ni asi nitāj si nikāj ni ‘ngō formación técnica;


;make Mozilla contributors proud of what we're doing and motivate us to continue; and
nù yikïn ñûnj na’nga ñûnj riña nej duguî’ rugûñu’ūnj riña Mozilla da’ ganïn ruhuâ nej si sisī ‘ngō sun du’uē xi huin sa dugu’nïn’ ñûnj ri ñûnj da’ dugu’nïn’ sun nan gan’an ne’ ñāan; nī


;provide a framework for other people to advance this vision of the Internet.
naga’uì’ ñûnj ‘ngō nuguan’ hue’ê riña a’ngô nej duguî’ da’ ganïn ruhuâ si dàj rû’ anïn ruhuâ ñûnj ni’in ñûnj Internet.


;These principles will not come to life on their own. People are needed to make the Internet open and participatory - people acting as individuals, working together in groups, and leading others. The Mozilla Foundation is committed to advancing the principles set out in the Mozilla Manifesto. We invite others to join us and make the Internet an ever better place for everyone.
Nej dukuàn nan nī sê màn si gachīj ma’an ‘ngoj gan’an. Dañùn ni’ñan nej duguî’ a’nïn nimâ sisī Internet nī da’ui ga ni’nïn nī gahuin si’iaj darûn’: duguî’ huā nikā hia ruhuâ nī nihià’ ruhuâ si gi‘iaj sun nugua’àn si nī hua ruhuâ si rugûñu’ūnj si a’ngô da’āj dugui’ si. Fundación Mozilla nī rikij ‘ngō si nuguàn’anj sisī da’ui digahuin daran’ chre nej nuguan’ huin ‘ngo si dukuànj Mozilla. Yi’ì dan nī nakïn ñûnj a’ngô da’āj nej duguî’ ruhuâ nakāj dugui’ ngà ñûnj da’ nagi’iaj hue’ê nê’ doj Internet guendâ riña daran’ chre nê’.


;Principles
Chrēj nikò’ ñûnj


;Individuals must have the ability to shape the Internet and their own experiences on the Internet.
Nej guìi nī da’ui ni ganikāj ni rà ni da’ nadunā ni dàj gā internet nī dàj gachē nu hue’ê ni doj riñanj.


;Advancing the Mozilla Manifesto
Huāj ñûnj ne’ ñāan ngà nej chrēj gānikò’ Mozilla


;There are many different ways of advancing the principles of the Mozilla Manifesto. We welcome a broad range of activities, and anticipate the same creativity that Mozilla participants have shown in other areas of the project. For individuals not deeply involved in the Mozilla project, one basic and very effective way to support the Manifesto is to use Mozilla Firefox and other products that embody the principles of the Manifesto.
Ûta ga’ì hua sun gi’iô’ da’ gahui nej chrēj nikò’ Mozilla gan’an ne’ ñaan. Yi’ì dan guruhuâ ta’u nej su na’níït ‘ngō si nuguàn’ant numân nī nej sun ri nej su ne’ ñaan ngà Mozilla nī ngà daran’ sa rirà nej su da’ nahuin nìko gan’an. ‘Ngō nuguan’ huāj riña nej duguî’ nitāj si ‘iaj sun nìko ‘ngà Mozilla huin sisī achín nì’iaj ñûnj riña nej su da’ ga’ue gachīj chrēj nan gan’an nī gi’iaj su ‘ngō sunūj u nī garasuunt dòj Mozilla Firefox ngà nej rasun nika nī ngà nej chrej nìkoj hua.


;Mozilla Foundation Pledge
